      "writtenOn": "2016-04-28T21:39:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "true here means that ThreadLooper owns it and will delete the looper on thread exit.\n(1) are you sure EmulatorQtWindow or anything else won\u0027t have access to a dangling pointer at that time?\n(2) please make sure the EmulatorQtWindow object is created on the same thread as it will be running. otherwise that other thread would get no Qt looper",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 136,
        "startChar": 52,
        "endLine": 136,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "3915b6b5588d1360201fa36d8f7020bd4678ad8f",
