        "id": 1078773
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-05-02T18:03:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1) Yes, that\u0027s fine. The situation is exactly the same as before, the only thing that changed is the place where the looper is created. The looper used to be created withing winsys-qt, but I had to move it here because now EmulatorQtWindow needs it in order to be created, and EmulatorQtWidow::getInstance is invoked by winsys-qt a bit earlier.\n2) EmulatorQtWindow is effectively created within winsys-qt, it\u0027s the UI thread",
      "parentUuid": "88e9e5fc_65376ed4",
      "range": {
